Created ExcelToPowerPoint.bas module for Excel-to-PowerPoint conversion

Saved to ExcelToPowerPoint.bas. Here's how to use it:

Setup (one-time)
Open your Excel workbook
Alt+F11 to open the VBA editor
File → Import File → select ExcelToPowerPoint.bas
Close the VBA editor
Configure
Edit the SheetConfig() function at the top — add/remove entries to match your tab names:

SheetConfig = Array( _
    Array("Sales Summary",  "Sales Summary"), _
    Array("Revenue Chart",  "Revenue Analysis"), _
    Array("KPIs",           "") _   ' empty string = no title bar
)

Run
Alt+F8 → select ExportToPowerPoint → Run

Output saves automatically next to your workbook as <WorkbookName>_slides.pptx.

What it handles
Content	How
Tables with cell formatting, colors, borders	CopyPicture — exact screen render
Embedded charts in a worksheet	Captured in the same picture
Chart sheets (standalone chart tabs)	Uses ChartArea.Copy instead
Objects/images that extend past the data range	ExpandRangeToObjects grows the copy area to include them
Varying sizes	Scales each slide's picture uniformly to fill the slide
Note: Save your workbook as .xlsm (macro-enabled) if you want to keep the macro inside the file. Otherwise, the .bas file is the portable version you can re-import anytime.